 <section xml:id="what-is-alp">
  <title>What is the &alp;?</title>
  <para>
   The &alp; (ALP) is a lightweight operating system. Instead of applications distributed in
   traditional software packages, it runs containerized and virtualized workloads.
  </para>
 </section>
 <section xml:id="how-it-works-alp">
  <title>How does the &alp; work?</title>
  <para>
   The &alp; (ALP) consists of an immutable base operating system and an orchestrator.
   The orchestrator manages and runs containers on top of the base OS. These containers
   contain various workloads, for example applications or a complete development environment.
   ALP supports several orchestrator types, for example &k3s; or Podman.
  </para>
